Steven B Stillwell was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Steven B Stillwell was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Application for Governor's Requisition, Wanted for Trial - Normal

Defendant Steven B Stillwell in court, in custody, with attorney Jeremy J Guza.   Stephen Joseph Centinario appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant does not challenge the extradition and would like to go back to the State of Georgia. State provides the Governor's Warrant to the Court. Bail is revoked and the State of Georgia can have the defendant. Defendant is remanded to the State of Georgia police.
